  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> tomato[es]</strong> roughly</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-bacon-and-pepper-wholewheat-spaghetti-with-crispy-capers/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Pat your<strong> capers </strong>dry<strong> </strong>with kitchen paper</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> capers</strong> to the pan and cook for 6-7 min or until crispy, then season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Once crispy, transfer the<strong> crispy capers</strong> to a plate and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-bacon-and-pepper-wholewheat-spaghetti-with-crispy-capers/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>in<strong> </strong>250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[350ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>stock</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese </strong>finely</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-bacon-and-pepper-wholewheat-spaghetti-with-crispy-capers/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon lardons</strong> and<strong> diced pepper</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until golden and crisp</p><p>Reboil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-bacon-and-pepper-wholewheat-spaghetti-with-crispy-capers/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the lardons are crispy, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Once slightly softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and<strong> chopped tomato </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until the tomato has completely softened</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-bacon-and-pepper-wholewheat-spaghetti-with-crispy-capers/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>wholewheat</strong> <strong>spaghetti </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>wholewheat</strong> <strong>spaghetti</strong> for 7-9 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>wholewheat</strong> <strong>spaghetti</strong>, reserving 80ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [100ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[120ml]</span> <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-bacon-and-pepper-wholewheat-spaghetti-with-crispy-capers/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the tomato has completely softened, add the <strong>stock</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 7-8 min or until the sauce has thickened and everything's completely tender – this is your <strong>tomatoey bacon & pepper sauce</strong></p><p>Stir the <strong>drained wholewheat spaghetti</strong> through the sauce with the <strong>reserved starchy pasta water</strong> – this is your <strong>tomatoey bacon & pepper wholewheat spaghetti</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Keep the sauce and pasta separate!</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-bacon-and-pepper-wholewheat-spaghetti-with-crispy-capers/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>tomatoey bacon & pepper wholewheat spaghetti</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>grated cheese</strong> and <strong>crispy capers</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave the crispy capers!</span></strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
